    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-03-14T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-03-14T16:00:00-05:00" n="1220"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1220">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.142/1460</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SWG1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d1220fn1">The same to the Ambassador in Great
                        Britain, No. 3036.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-14T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 14, 1916, 4 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1422. Ascertain whether Government to which you are accredited will permit
                    landing medical supplies for Jewish hospitals in Jerusalem by United States
                    naval collier at Jaffa. Turkish Government consents on condition no member of
                    crew goes ashore and no one from shore goes on board collier.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
